// FX-8b — lint-prefetch-unresolved fixture (W-CG-CHUNK-PREFETCH-UNRESOLVED)
// File 2/2 — About route ("/about"). Sibling page that exists in
// the compile unit; needed so RouteMap.pages.size > 1 (the lint
// gating condition). About has its OWN internal link back to "/" —
// which DOES resolve to the sibling index.scrml — so this page's
// `hasPrefetchableLinks` is true and NO PREFETCH lint fires for it.
// This lets §5 of the test verify the lint-emission case-discrimination
// is per-EP (NOT global to the compile unit).

<program title="Prefetch-Unresolved About">

<nav class="flex items-center gap-3 p-4 border-b">
  <h1 class="text-xl font-semibold">About</h1>
  <a href="/" class="text-blue-600">Home (resolves)</a>
</nav>

<section class="p-4">
  <p class="text-sm text-slate-600">
    Has a resolving internal link to "/". Therefore neither
    PREFETCH lint fires for this page — only the home page's
    unresolved links surface the warning.
  </p>
</section>

</program>
